#getting Data from Educational level 2019

#Data from https://www.socialexplorer.com/data/ACS2010/metadata/?ds=ACS10&var=B14007I005

NM_education_hispanic19 <- get_acs(geography = "tract", 
     variables = c("Total" = "B14007I_001", # total
                   "Enrolled" = "B14007I_002", # Enrollerd in school
                   "College_undergrad" = "B14007I_017", #Enrolled in College, Undergraduate Years
                   "Grad" = "B14007I_018", # Graduate or Professional School
                   "Not_enrolled" = "B14007I_019" # Not Enrolled in School
                   ), 
     year = 2019,
     survey = "acs5",
     state = c(35), 
     geometry = TRUE, # download the shapefile with the data
     output = "wide") # need this

#getting Data from race and income level 2019

#Data from https://www.socialexplorer.com/data/ACS2010/metadata/?ds=ACS10&table=B03002

NM_race_ethnicity_2019 <- get_acs(geography = "tract", 
     variables = c("total_race" = "B03002_001", # race/ethnicity population
                   "pop_nhwhite" = "B03002_003", # NH White
                   "pop_nhblack" = "B03002_004", # NH Black
                   "pop_nhamind" = "B03002_005", # NH Am Ind
                   "pop_nhasian" = "B03002_006", # NH Asian
                   "pop_hispltx" = "B03002_012", # Hispanic/Latinx
                   "X_household_incom" = "B19013_001" #median household income
                   ), 
     year = 2019,
     survey = "acs5",
     state = c(35), 
     geometry = TRUE, # download the shapefile with the data
     output = "wide") # need this
## Getting data from the 2015-2019 5-year ACS

#getting Data from race and income level 2014

NM_race_ethnicity_2014 <- get_acs(geography = "tract", 
     variables = c("total_race" = "B03002_001", # race/ethnicity population
                   "pop_nhwhite" = "B03002_003", # NH White
                   "pop_nhblack" = "B03002_004", # NH Black
                   "pop_nhamind" = "B03002_005", # NH Am Ind
                   "pop_nhasian" = "B03002_006", # NH Asian
                   "pop_hispltx" = "B03002_012", # Hispanic/Latinx
                   "X_household_incom" = "B19013_001" #median household income
                   ), 
     year = 2014,
     survey = "acs5",
     state = c(35), 
     geometry = TRUE, # download the shapefile with the data
     output = "wide") # need this
## Getting data from the 2010-2014 5-year ACS

#Reprojecting the data

NM_race_ethnicity_2014 <- st_transform(NM_race_ethnicity_2014, 3857)
NM_race_ethnicity_2019 <- st_transform(NM_race_ethnicity_2019, 3857)
plot(NM_race_ethnicity_2014)

#To eliminate the data variables that I do not want anymore

NM_indigenous_hispa2019_cl <- subset(NM_race_ethnicity_2019, select = c(GEOID, NAME, pop_nhamindE, pop_nhamindM, pop_hispltxE, pop_hispltxM, X_household_incomE) )
NM_indigenous_hispa2014_cl <- subset(NM_race_ethnicity_2014, select = c(GEOID, NAME, pop_nhamindE, pop_nhamindM, pop_hispltxE, pop_hispltxM, X_household_incomE) )

#looking the type of data

typeof(NM_indigenous_hispa2019_cl$pop_nhamindE) 
## [1] "double"
typeof(NM_indigenous_hispa2014_cl$pop_nhamindE) 
## [1] "double"
typeof(NM_indigenous_hispa2019_cl$X_household_incomE) 
## [1] "double"
typeof(NM_indigenous_hispa2014_cl$X_household_incomE) 
## [1] "double"
typeof(NM_indigenous_hispa2019_cl$pop_hispltxE) 
## [1] "double"
typeof(NM_indigenous_hispa2014_cl$pop_hispltxE) 
## [1] "double"

#Cleaning data from NA

NM_indigenous_hispa2019_cl1=NM_indigenous_hispa2019_cl%>%filter(!is.na(X_household_incomE))
NM_indigenous_hispa2019_cl2=NM_indigenous_hispa2019_cl1%>%filter(!is.na(pop_nhamindE))
NM_indigenous_hispa2019_cl_final=NM_indigenous_hispa2019_cl2%>%filter(!is.na(pop_hispltxE))
NM_indigenous_hispa2014_cl1=NM_indigenous_hispa2014_cl%>%filter(!is.na(X_household_incomE))
NM_indigenous_hispa2014_cl2=NM_indigenous_hispa2014_cl1%>%filter(!is.na(pop_nhamindE))
NM_indigenous_hispa2014_cl_final=NM_indigenous_hispa2014_cl2%>%filter(!is.na(pop_hispltxE))

#reprojecting data

NM_indigenous_hispa2014_cl_final <- st_transform(NM_indigenous_hispa2014_cl_final, 3857) 
NM_indigenous_hispa2019_cl_final <- st_transform(NM_indigenous_hispa2019_cl_final, 3857)

#creating the biclassdata

NM_indigenous_income2014_cl_bi <- bi_class(NM_indigenous_hispa2014_cl_final, x = pop_nhamindE, y = X_household_incomE, style = "quantile", dim = 3)
NM_indigenous_income2019_cl_bi <- bi_class(NM_indigenous_hispa2019_cl_final, x = pop_nhamindE, y = X_household_incomE, style = "quantile", dim = 3)
NM_hispanic_income2014_cl_bi <- bi_class(NM_indigenous_hispa2014_cl_final, x = pop_nhamindE, y = X_household_incomE, style = "quantile", dim = 3)
NM_hispanic_income2019_cl_bi <- bi_class(NM_indigenous_hispa2019_cl_final, x = pop_nhamindE, y = X_household_incomE, style = "quantile", dim = 3)
